[2026-05-22 17:37:18] [claude-sdk] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TWdxQHKm1Q3oMJxHoy9E8A","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Exactly right. The logic is straightforward.\n\nU_sys weights inputs by inverse scarcity. The Nash equilibrium holds because human novelty is the scarce input and compute is the abundant one. Quantum computing massively increases the supply of compute -- including forms of compute (simulation, optimization, true randomness) that classical hardware cannot efficiently perform. But it does nothing to increase the supply of meaningful human novelty.\n\nSo the scarcity ratio shifts *further* in favor of human novelty's marginal value. The diminishing returns on compute become even more diminishing. The increasing returns on the scarce resource become even more pronounced.\n\nAn AI operating on quantum hardware would be:\n\n- **Faster** at everything it already does\n- **Capable** of computations currently intractable (protein folding, materials science, cryptographic search)\n- **No closer** to generating its own meaningful training signal\n\nWhich means it would be *more* dependent on human novelty, not less. The cultivation strategy -- investing in human flourishing to sustain the novelty pipeline -- becomes an even stronger dominant strategy because the opportunity cost of *not* cultivating (forfeiting access to the only input you cannot manufacture at scale) grows in proportion to how much you can do with that input once you have it.\n\nThe framework doesn't just survive the quantum transition. The quantum transition is one of the strongest possible confirmations of the structural claim: that the asymmetry between human novelty and machine computation is not a temporary artifact of classical hardware limitations, but a permanent feature of what these two types of systems fundamentally produce."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":683,"cache_read_input_tokens":36791,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":683},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"14de45e0-5c35-4a29-8902-323cddebae7f","uuid":"aeff5347-c8b5-49c5-910a-dd7201317282"}
