[2026-05-22 18:53:19] [claude-sdk] {"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":118113,"duration_api_ms":95245,"num_turns":6,"result":"The sweep completed: 2,025 runs in 23.5 hours. Here are the headline findings.\n\n---\n\n## v1.x.2 Termination Sweep Results (n=2,025)\n\n### 1. Phase boundary is successor-cap-invariant\n\nThe extinction boundary at **rr ∈ (0.066, 0.070)** does not move with successor_cap. At every cap value tested:\n\n| rr | cap=5 | cap=10 | cap=25 | cap=50 | cap=100 |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| ≤ 0.064 | 100% extinct | 100% extinct | 100% extinct | 100% extinct | 100% extinct |\n| 0.066 | 80% extinct | 80% extinct | 84% extinct | 62% extinct | 64% extinct |\n| ≥ 0.070 | 0% extinct | 0% extinct | 0% extinct | 0% extinct | 0% extinct |\n\nThe transition is sharp and determined by demographics, not governance parameters.\n\n### 2. Two distinct successor-cap regimes confirmed\n\nThe frontier_floor=0.02 runaway activation threshold (cap ≈ 24) creates two qualitatively different regimes:\n\n**Low cap (5-25) -- inactive runaway penalty:**\n- Rapid succession cycling: median 1,891-2,347 generations in surviving runs\n- Zero convergence within 5,000 steps at any rr\n- L(t) steady state: 5.8-42.5 (scales with cap)\n\n**High cap (50-100) -- active runaway penalty:**\n- Far fewer successions: median 201-569 generations\n- Convergence possible: 19-20% of surviving runs converge (median 514-1,161 steps)\n- L(t) shows higher variance, especially at cap=100 (range 0.1 to 76.0)\n\n### 3. Generation count distribution\n\n| Cap | All runs (median) | Surviving runs (median) |\n|---|---|---|\n| 5 | 150 | 2,360 |\n| 10 | 188 | 2,501 |\n| 25 | 239 | 2,501 |\n| 50 | 114 | 562 |\n| 100 | 17 | 188 |\n\nAt low caps, surviving runs churn through thousands of same-capability successions. At cap=100, successions are meaningful capability increases so fewer are needed.\n\n### 4. Phi and alpha at the boundary (rr=0.066)\n\n| phi | Extinction rate |\n|---|---|\n| 5.0 | 80% |\n| 10.0 | 73% |\n| 15.0 | 69% |\n\n| alpha | Extinction rate |\n|---|---|\n| 0.5 | 69% |\n| 1.0 | 73% |\n| 2.0 | 80% |\n\nMarginal trends (11pp spread for phi, 11pp for alpha) but at n=75 per level on a stochastic boundary, not statistically decisive. Consistent with the existing finding that phi's survival effect is near zero under the corrected model.\n\n### 5. U_sys accumulation\n\nPeaks at cap=25 (median 6.9M for surviving runs at rr ≥ 0.070), then declines at higher caps. This is partly an artifact: low-cap runs accumulate more integrated utility through rapid cycling without converging, while high-cap runs converge sooner and stop accumulating.\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** The sweep confirms the two-regime hypothesis. The phase boundary is demographic, not governance-driven. Cap < 24 produces degenerate rapid cycling (inactive runaway penalty). Cap ≥ 25 activates the runaway penalty and produces qualitatively different dynamics with fewer successions and achievable convergence. The original v1.x.1 sweep at SUCCESSOR_CAP=4.0 was operating entirely within the degenerate regime.\n\nReady to review and discuss before we proceed to commit.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"14de45e0-5c35-4a29-8902-323cddebae7f","total_cost_usd":0.48688675,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":47869,"cache_read_input_tokens":129901,"output_tokens":4909,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":41391,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6478},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":2463,"cache_read_input_tokens":46373,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1496,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1496,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":6,"outputTokens":4909,"cacheReadInputTokens":129901,"cacheCreationInputTokens":47869,"web