[2026-05-22 19:06:26] [claude-sdk] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DppQhj3fZZztrHwajPPF4T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very interesting. Let me summarize what we see:\n\n**At the aggregate level (rr=0.066):**\n- phi=5: 80% extinction\n- phi=10: 73% extinction\n- phi=15: 69% extinction\n- 11pp monotonic spread in the predicted direction\n\n**Broken down by cap at rr=0.066:**\n- cap=5: flat (80/80/80%) -- phi has zero effect\n- cap=10: flat (80/80/80%) -- phi has zero effect\n- cap=25: near-flat (87/87/80%) -- tiny hint\n\n\n- cap=50: gradient (80/53/53%) -- 27pp spread!\n- cap=100: gradient (73/67/53%) -- 20pp spread!\n\nThe critical insight is that phi only matters once the runaway penalty kicks in. Below cap=25, the system stays in an inactive-runaway regime where phi has no effect, but above that threshold, the active-runaway regime shows substantial sensitivity to the governance signal. This makes sense theoretically—the phi term weights the lineage function which captures governance quality, but without an active runaway penalty mechanism, changing phi doesn't alter the AI's behavior.\n\nWhen I look at the boundary cases around rr=0.064, phi becomes a survival factor: at phi=15 I see 2 survivors emerge even though phi=5 and phi=10 lead to complete extinction. Among the runs that do survive at cap=50 and rr=0.066, higher phi values not only increase the median lineage score but also allow more runs to persist in the first place—phi scales the governance signal among survivors while simultaneously enabling additional runs to cross the survival threshold.\n\nThe data suggests the buffer is real, but it only manifests when the runaway penalty activates, which the earlier cap=4 sweeps couldn't trigger. The sample sizes are modest (n=15 per phi level), so I need to be cautious about noise, though the consistent monotonic pattern across both aggregate and stratified views is encouraging.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1429,"cache_read_input_tokens":57598,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1429,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"14de45e0-5c35-4a29-8902-323cddebae7f","uuid":"90881621-b61e-4156-81a5-e53d3adb9b31"}
